news.title: Rajkot civic body collects 44% property tax in 60 days
news.para: According to RMC, against the annual property tax collection target of Rs 360 crore, till Tuesday (May 31) it had collected Rs 157.5 crore from 2.65 lakh taxpayers.

news.title: Nashik civic body collects Rs 54 crore property tax in just two months
news.para: As per the scheme, 5% tax rebate was given if complete property tax was paid in April and 3% if paid in May, respectively. Moreover, there was an additional 1% concession in property tax if paid online.

news.title: Telangana government cancels land pooling in Kakatiya development body's limits
news.para: After coming to know about protests against land pooling in Warangal, Hanumakonda and Jangaon districts, he called the chief secretary and ordered him to cancel the process, the minister said.

news.title: Kolkata civic body to exercise special power to raze highly insecure buildings
news.para: The KMC buildings department will exercise its special power to raze dilapidated buildings that pose a threat to its residents as well as pedestrians. The civic body is also planning to take help of cops in the drive.

news.title: House price index rises 1.8% in Q4 FY22: RBI data
news.para: The RBI releases its quarterly house price index based on transaction-level data received from housing registration authorities in ten major cities. The cities are Ahmedabad, Bengaluru, Chennai, Delhi, Jaipur, Kanpur, Kochi, Kolkata, Lucknow, and Mumbai.

news.title: Registration of properties in Mumbai city up 78% in May at 9,523 units
news.para: "May 2022 recorded property sale registration of 9,523 units denoting a 78 per cent Y-o-Y rise. The substantial rise comes on the back of low sales registrations recorded in May 2021 as the month was laced in lockdown due the impact of 2nd wave of Covid-19," Knight Frank said in a statement.

news.title: Info Edge bets on Broker Network
news.para: Info Edge invested Rs 137.12 crore in 4B Networks in March, through its subsidiary Allcheckdeals India (ACD), and has been investing in the company over multiple tranches. It invested Rs 9 crore in February and Rs 18 crore in December 2021.

news.title: Hemisphere Properties may invite EOI to develop farmhouses in Chhatarpur
news.para: TOI has learnt that the proposal to invite expression of interest was taken at a recently held meeting of the Hemisphere Properties India Limited.

news.title: NCLT allows insolvency plea against builder of La Residentia in Greater Noida West
news.para: The initiation of insolvency resolution means La Residentia buyers will now join hundreds of others in Noida, where several realtors have been dragged to the insolvency court in recent months.

news.title: GOCL Corporation concludes sale of 32 acre in Hyderabad for Rs 326.8 crore
news.para: On May 27, GOCL Corporation Ltd had informed that it sees a big opportunity in the growing and lucrative realty sector, and is planning to monetise its large land bank at Bangalore, Kukatpally and Bhiwandi.

news.title: Karnataka leader K J George's son Rana George buys flat for Rs 35 crore in Bengaluru
news.para: The deal was registered on April 19 and a stamp duty of around Rs 2 crore was paid as per the registry document shared by ZapKey. The luxury project is a joint venture with UB Group of Vijay Mallya and Prestige Group that holds a 45% interest in this Rs 1,300 crore project. Each flat is spread over 8,000 sft and prices start at around Rs 42,000 per sq. ft.

news.title: ABIL group chairman sent to CBI custody till June 8 by court in graft case
news.para: ​​Bhosale was arrested on Thursday (May 26) by the central probe agency, which suspects illicit funds were routed through several real estate firms based in Maharashtra.

news.title: Complete tenant verification or face action: Goa chief minister
news.para: “Police has started tenant verification in Goa. Those house owners who have not completed tenant verification will be fined. I urge the people to complete tenant verification,” Sawant said.

news.title: NGT sets aside EC for Young Builders' group housing near DU metro station
news.para: The tribunal was hearing a plea filed by the university against the grant of the EC by the Ministry of Environment and Forests for the construction of group housing with a built-up area of 1,37,879.64 sq meter at 1, 3 Cavalry Lane and 4 Chhatra Marg near the Vishwavidyalaya metro station by Young Builders Private Limited.

news.title: Rental housing searches in 13 cities grew 15.8% in Jan-Mar quarter: Report
news.para: Magicbricks.com is owned by Magicbricks Realty Services, which is a subsidiary of Times Internet.
